  "text": "MMPs are secreted from cells as inactive forms known as proMMPs. Some inactive MMPs are found bound to the extracellular matrix, which allows their quick activation. MMP-2 binds to extracellular matrix containing elastin. MMP-3 binds to the basal membrane and occasionally to collagen fibrils while MMP-13 binds to proteoglycans, collagen and elastin [CITATION_1] . Forms of \"storage\" are not the same for all MMPs. For example, MMP-8 is stored in specific cell granules, while MMP-1 and MMP-3 are constitutively produced by the activities of cytokines and inflammatory mediators [CITATION_2] .",
